  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 433894a244f646848a22a9c7d127b66b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Coming Judgment against Judah'
      title: Coming Judgment against Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Zephaniah
        when Josiah son of Amon was king of Judah. Zephaniah was the son of Cushi,
        son of Gedaliah, son of Amariah, son of Hezekiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI will sweep away everythingfrom the face of the earth,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI will sweep away people and animals alike.I will sweep away
        the birds of the sky and the fish in the sea.I will reduce the wicked to
        heaps of rubble,[[COMMENT(0)]]and I will wipe humanity from the face of the
        earth,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI will crush Judah and Jerusalem with my fistand destroy every
        last trace of their Baal worship.I will put an end to all the idolatrous
        priests,so that even the memory of them will disappear.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For they go up to their roofsand bow down to the sun, moon, and stars.They
        claim to follow the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but then they worship Molech,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        too.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Malcam, </b>a variant spelling of Molech; or it could
          possibly mean <b>their king.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And I will destroy those who used to worship mebut now no longer
        do.They no longer ask for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s guidanceor
        seek my blessings.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Stand in silence in the presence of the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for
        the awesome day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s judgment is near.The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has prepared his people for a great slaughterand
        has chosen their executioners.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>has prepared a sacrifice and sanctified his guests.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201COn that day of judgment,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201CI
        will punish the leaders and princes of Judahand all those following pagan
        customs.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Yes, I will punish those who participate in pagan worship ceremonies,and
        those who fill their masters\u2019 houses with violence and deceit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201COn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Ca
        cry of alarm will come from the Fish Gateand echo throughout the New Quarter
        of the city.[[COMMENT(0)]]And a great crash will sound from the hills.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: Or <b>the Second Quarter, </b>a newer section of Jerusalem. Hebrew
          reads <b>the Mishneh.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Wail in sorrow, all you who live in the market area,[[COMMENT(0)]]for
        all the merchants and traders will be destroyed.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: Or <b>in the valley, </b>a lower section of Jerusalem. Hebrew reads
          <b>the Maktesh.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI will search with lanterns in Jerusalem\u2019s darkest cornersto
        punish those who sit complacent in their sins.They think the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will do nothing to them,either good or bad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So their property will be plundered,their homes will be ransacked.They
        will build new homesbut never live in them.They will plant vineyardsbut never
        drink wine from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThat terrible day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is near.Swiftly
        it comes\u2014a day of bitter tears,a day when even strong men will cry out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "It will be a day when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger
        is poured out\u2014a day of terrible distress and anguish,a day of ruin and
        desolation,a day of darkness and gloom,a day of clouds and blackness,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'a day of trumpet calls and battle cries.Down go the walled citiesand
        the strongest battlements!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBecause you have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,I
        will make you grope around like the blind.Your blood will be poured into
        the dust,and your bodies will lie rotting on the ground.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Your silver and gold will not save youon that day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anger.For the whole land will be devouredby the fire of his jealousy.He will
        make a terrifying endof all the people on earth.[[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: Or <b>the people living in the land.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Call to Repentance'
      title: A Call to Repentance
      number: 1
      content: "  Gather together\u2014yes, gather together,you shameless nation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Gather before judgment begins,before your time to repent is blown
        away like chaff.Act now, before the fierce fury of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        fallsand the terrible day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger
        begins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Judgment against Philistia'
      title: Judgment against Philistia
      number: 3
      content: "Seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all who are humble,and follow
        his commands.Seek to do what is rightand to live humbly.Perhaps even yet
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will protect you\u2014protect you from his
        anger on that day of destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Gaza and Ashkelon will be abandoned,Ashdod and Ekron torn down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And what sorrow awaits you Philistines[[COMMENT(0)]]who live along
        the coast and in the land of Canaan,for this judgment is against you, too!The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will destroy youuntil not one of you is left.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Kerethites.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Philistine coast will become a wilderness pasture,a place of
        shepherd campsand enclosures for sheep and goats.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Judgment against Moab and Ammon'
      title: Judgment against Moab and Ammon
      number: 7
      content: 'The remnant of the tribe of Judah will pasture there.They will rest
        at night in the abandoned houses in Ashkelon.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God will visit his people in kindnessand restore their prosperity again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CI have heard the taunts of the Moabitesand the insults of the
        Ammonites,mocking my peopleand invading their borders.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now, as surely as I live,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel,\u201CMoab and Ammon will be destroyed\u2014destroyed
        as completely as Sodom and Gomorrah.Their land will become a place of stinging
        nettles,salt pits, and eternal desolation.The remnant of my people will plunder
        themand take their land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They will receive the wages of their pride,for they have scoffed
        at the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Judgment against Ethiopia and Assyria'
      title: Judgment against Ethiopia and Assyria
      number: 11
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will terrify themas he destroys all
        the gods in the land.Then nations around the world will worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,each
        in their own land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou Ethiopians[[COMMENT(0)]] will also be slaughteredby my
        sword,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cushites.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike the lands of the
        north with his fist,destroying the land of Assyria.He will make its great
        capital, Nineveh, a desolate wasteland,parched like a desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The proud city will become a pasture for flocks and herds,and all
        sorts of wild animals will settle there.The desert owl and screech owl will
        roost on its ruined columns,their calls echoing through the gaping windows.Rubble
        will block all the doorways,and the cedar paneling will be exposed to the
        weather.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "This is the boisterous city,once so secure.\u201CI am the greatest!\u201D
        it boasted.\u201CNo other city can compare with me!\u201DBut now, look how
        it has become an utter ruin,a haven for wild animals.Everyone passing by
        will laugh in derisionand shake a defiant fist."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jerusalem\u2019s Rebellion and Redemption"
      title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Rebellion and Redemption"
      number: 1
      content: '  What sorrow awaits rebellious, polluted Jerusalem,the city of violence
        and crime!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'No one can tell it anything;it refuses all correction.It does not
        trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>or draw near to its God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Its leaders are like roaring lionshunting for their victims.Its judges
        are like ravenous wolves at evening time,who by dawn have left no trace of
        their prey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Its prophets are arrogant liars seeking their own gain.Its priests
        defile the Temple by disobeying God\u2019s instructions.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is still there in the city,and
        he does no wrong.Day by day he hands down justice,and he does not fail.But
        the wicked know no shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI have wiped out many nations,devastating their fortress walls
        and towers.Their streets are now deserted;their cities lie in silent ruin.There
        are no survivors\u2014none at all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I thought, \u2018Surely they will have reverence for me now!Surely
        they will listen to my warnings.Then I won\u2019t need to strike again,destroying
        their homes.\u2019But no, they get up earlyto continue their evil deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore, be patient,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CSoon
        I will stand and accuse these evil nations.For I have decided to gather the
        kingdoms of the earthand pour out my fiercest anger and fury on them.All
        the earth will be devouredby the fire of my jealousy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThen I will purify the speech of all people,so that everyone
        can worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> together.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'My scattered people who live beyond the rivers of Ethiopia[[COMMENT(0)]]will
        come to present their offerings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cush.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On that day you will no longer need to be ashamed,for you will no
        longer be rebels against me.I will remove all proud and arrogant people from
        among you.There will be no more haughtiness on my holy mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Those who are left will be the lowly and humble,for it is they who
        trust in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The remnant of Israel will do no wrong;they will never tell lies
        or deceive one another.They will eat and sleep in safety,and no one will
        make them afraid.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Sing, O daughter of Zion;shout aloud, O Israel!Be glad and rejoice
        with all your heart,O daughter of Jerusalem!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will remove his hand of judgmentand
        will disperse the armies of your enemy.And the <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>himself,
        the King of Israel,will live among you!At last your troubles will be over,and
        you will never again fear disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "On that day the announcement to Jerusalem will be,\u201CCheer up,
        Zion! Don\u2019t be afraid!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is living among you.He
        is a mighty savior.He will take delight in you with gladness.With his love,
        he will calm all your fears.[[COMMENT(0)]]He will rejoice over you with joyful
        songs.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        content: Or <b>He will be silent in his love. </b>Greek and Syriac versions
          read <b>He will renew you with his love.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CI will gather you who mourn for the appointed festivals;you
        will be disgraced no more.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:18 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew for this verse is uncertain.
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will deal severely with all who have oppressed you.I will save
        the weak and helpless ones;I will bring togetherthose who were chased away.I
        will give glory and fame to my former exiles,wherever they have been mocked
        and shamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "On that day I will gather you togetherand bring you home again.I
        will give you a good name, a name of distinction,among all the nations of
        the earth,as I restore your fortunes before their very eyes.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
